properties.description: DNG Martin O'Connor Estate Agents are delighted to offer for sale a unique property holding on the Atlantic Coast. The property extending to the sea on two sides, consists of a dwelling house and a cottage on c. 8.68 Ha (21.44 Acres) of land with 360 degree uninterrupted sea views in addition to two half shares of two coastal island known as Oyster Rock and Illaunrossalough in an area of Connemara regarded for its rugged beauty and spectacular scenery. The property enjoys a picture perfect setting with the backdrop of the Maum Turks mountains & Loughaconeera Hill in the background and enjoys fantastic views of the The Twelve Pens while Kilkieran Bay encompasses this lovely peninsula which this property stands on. The property is split in two even sized sections by a boreen which leads to the Quay which also borders the land. The main dwelling facing southwards is perched on the highest point of the land where it enjoys the most incredible views imaginable over the Connemara Landscape. The house in need of total renovation provides the blank canvas to redevelop it into a stunning home with postcard picture views in all directions. The accommodation consists of a porch, hall, living room, kitchen, three bedrooms and a shower room. The property is connected to mains electricity, water and private drainage. The cottage across the road is also a south facing property which was the former homestead of the farm. It is a stone built building with a side shed. The property extending to the sea offers so much potential to redevelop, subject to planning permission, into another residence on the land for a family member, self catering unit or a work studio. The land unused for many years is displaying a lovely array of colour through its long grasses and heathers, enjoys considerable road frontage and offers the potential to use for grazing and to create a small farm holding. It is also the perfect opportunity for neighbouring farmers to expand their existing holdings as properties of this size rarely present themselves to the market in this lovely part of Connemara. The Quay at the end of the road was, in times gone by, used by local fishermen and farm families to gain access to other villages along the coast to get their daily needs, from fishing to tending to livestock and to go shopping. The sea surrounding the property is perfect for kayaking and other water based activities.The properties offering so much potential would make a super holiday home project within an hours drive of Galway City and three hours from Dublin and two hours from Shannon Airport. Furthermore, with the work from home possibilities, where better to work in total tranquility and yet be within easy commuting distance of major urban centres. The area is well served with broadband and for those with higher internet demand Udaras na Gaeltachta have, throughout Connemara, developed G Teic centres where one can avail of hot desks, meeting rooms, higher technology and much more which enables individuals grow their own business rurally and enjoy a wonderful rural lifestyle for a growing family with all essential needs on its doorstep. The villages of Carraroe & Carna are also only a 20 minute drive. The property is located within a short drive from local facilities which includes shops, hardware stores, national and second level schools, GAA playing fields, a doctors surgery and bars at Rosmuc while the seaside villages of Kilkieran, Carna, Casla and Carraroe are within easy driving distance. Viewings of this truly remarkable property are highly recommend to fully appreciate it unique setting and potential to develop in to spectacular seaside home. To arrange a viewing of this property, contact DNG Martin O'Connor on 091 866708.

Unique opportunity to acquire this multi unit property, consisting of, a two storey dwelling house, one bed apartment and detached self contained unit, all on one site. The entire property is situated in the heart of the Gealtacht area of Ring, Co. Waterford, close to Schools, The Cunnigar, Sandy Beaches, Boating Piers, ten minutes drive to Dungarvan Town and fifteen minutes drive to Ardmore Village. The opportunity presents many options for the discerning purchaser with the apartment attached to the main house which could be incorporated, transforming the main house into a substantial dwelling, or to take the investment approach capitalising on each one of the three separate entities available.The main house is in need of modernising but has huge potential with spacious rooms throughout with a fantastic sunny south aspect to the private rear garden. The apartment has been used as a rental property up to recently and is in good condition throughout and is to be sold with vacant possession.The self contained unit has not been used recently and very little decoration will get this unit up to standard.This property can be sold in three separate lots or the entire.Viewing Strictly by Appointment. The term Gaeltacht  refers to those regions of Ireland in which the Irish language (Gaeilge) is still spoken as a community language, and where Irish culture and tradition are very much alive and thriving. Each region possesses an environment, rich with heritage and folklore, culture and traditions and has a strong sense of its own identity and uniqueness.In County Waterford there is a small Gaeltacht region known as An Rinn. This small coastal Gaeltacht overlooks Dungarvan Harbour and is approximately six miles from there. It is a world apart - in its welcoming people, its scenery, its seascape and above all its cultural vitality. The love of Irish music, song, dance and language is infectious in An Rinn. A spontaneous desire to share tradition with the visitor can erupt at any time in friendly Ring Hostelry. For hikers or bikers, walkers or bird watchers, Ring and Old Parish are hideaways of cliff top trails, unspoiled beaches, inland drumlins and leafy glens. Add to this a hospitable people, and effervescent culture, and everything that makes the Gaeltacht different is on the doorstep.Leave Dungarvan heading west on the N25 towards Cork. Turn left on the R674, signposted An Rinn (Ring) and continue.An Cuinigear, signposted left, leads to a sand and shingle beach from which a wonderful 5km peninsula stretches into Dungarvan Bay. A great variety of seabirds can be observed along this narrow stretch of land which offers an enchanting and very scenic walk An Coinigéar Walk. Views embrace the full sweep of Dungarvan Bay with the dramatic backdrop of the Comeragh Mountains.Continue on this narrow road to arrive at the imposing edifice which is Coláiste na Rinne, an Irish Language College which is in operation since 1909. Full term (academic year) and summer courses are run in the language.

properties.description: DNG Begley are delighted to bring to the market this magnificent substantial detached residence located on the old Dublin Road at Ardnapondra on the outskirts of Moate Town. This magnificent house offers accommodation of 450m2 / 4550ft 2 across 3 floors. The detached garage to the rear of the property offers additional space of 144m2 /1550ft which provides the option of 4 additional bedrooms with en-suites. The house sits on a substantial large site of just over 4 acres, triangular in shape with over 200m of road frontage onto the old Dublin Road, it offers the potential for development of another site/property (subject to planning permission) or the potential for keeping 1-2 horses. Upon entering the property through the double front doors you enter the fabulous light filled hallway with its beautiful spiraling staircase up to 3 levels. The ground floor with its open plan kitchen/ breakfast and dining room is ideal for both family life and for entertainment. Double doors from the hallway lead to courtyard area which is fully decked out and has inbuilt BBQ and is an ideal west facing sheltered area for entertaining. The spacious sitting room and conservatory area with wood burning stove are the perfect places to relax. On the first floor landing there are double doors open to the balcony to the front of the property. The master bedroom includes a wonderful large en-suite with bath, separate shower and his and her sinks. Also on this floor are an additional 2 bedrooms both with en-suite, family bathroom, a large walk in wardrobe and a further bedroom and storage room. The second floor has two additional rooms which could be utilized as bedrooms or variety of other uses. The property is just 1.5km from centre of Moate which has some wonderful facilities & amenities including excellent secondary school, a fabulous 18 hole parkland gold course, Tuar ard Theatre and Arts Centre, Midland Amenity Park and Dun Na Si Heritage Park, Old Rail Trail Cycleway, supermarket along with many other small shops and pubs. The town of Athlone is only a 15 mins drive away offering all the services of a larger town. The property is also only 1km from Junction 6 on the M6 Motorway and exactly half way between Dublin (106km) and Galway (106km). The expansive accommodation comprises: Ground Floor: - Large Open Plan Kitchen Breakfast Room (8.6m x 4.4m) - Dining Room surrounded on 3 sides by floor to ceiling windows (5.1m x 3.6m) - Laundry Room (3.7m x 2.4m) - Guest Bedroom (3.7m x 2.8m) - Bathroom (2.2m x 1.7m) - Large Sitting Room with solid fuel stove (8.5m 4.4m) - Conservatory (5m x 3.6m) First Floor - Master Bedroom (5.7m x 4.2m) with large en-suite (5m x 3.7m) and walk in wardrobe (2.6m 2.1m) - Bedroom 3 (4.3m x 4.2m) with en-suite (3.8m x 2.7m) - Bedroom 4 (4.2m x 4m) with en-suite (3.8m x 2.8m) - Bedroom 5 (4.9m x 4.7m) - Walk in Wardrobe / Store (3.5m x2.4m) - Bathroom (3m x 2.2m) Second Floor - 2 Large rooms (4.85m x 4.5m X 2) Viewing by appointment only with DNG Begley.

properties.description: DNG Cyril Burke is delighted to bring to the market this unique opportunity to acquire this c. 1 acre site. The site is subject to planning permission. The site is located in the popular and sought after area of Gneeve which is located in Breaffy Castlebar. The site is elevated and has stunning views of Manulla and Breaffy.

DNG Cyril Burke Estate Agents are delighted to bring this 0.55 acre site to the market for sale by Private Treaty. Planning was granted under Planning Ref No. P07/18560 for the construction of a 2100 sq ft dormer type dwelling house, septic tank, proprietary effluent treatment unit and percolation area. A decision to extend the planning was granted in March 2012. Ballyglass is centrally located, 17 kms from Castlebar, 14 kms from Claremorris town centre and also within driving range of Galway City for work purposes and has a good road network. Ballyglass has excellent local amenities with a primary school, church, community centre and public house within walking distance of the site. Lough Cara is located a short drive away which is famous in the angling community as a top rate wild brown trout fishery with spectacular views of the surrounding countryside.

DNG Cyril Burke is delighted to bring to the market c.12 acres of agricultural land for sale by private treaty. The land is located in the townland of Ballinlassa which is in close proximity to the village of Belcarra. Belcarra is c. 6 miles south of Castlebar town. This is good quality arable land and is partly suitable for grazing or growing silage/ hay. The land is available for all farm scheme applications. Viewing is strictly by appointment only. To arrange a viewing contact DNG Cyril Burke.

A well established restaurant / bar for sale in Charlestown. The Cosy Bar and Restaurant is situated in the heart of Charlestown which comprises a thoroughfare of local shops with private residences close by. The business is long established and is being sold as a going concern. It is centrally located off the busy main N5 road located a mere 8 kms from Ireland West Airport. The Cosy Bar and Restaurant enjoys a thriving local business with a prosperous passing trade.There is potential to grow the existing business with room for an extension to the rear. Currently the restaurant enjoys a busy lunch trade and serves dinner till late. There is scope for the new owner to live in the property as there is accommodation upstairs to include 2 bedrooms and a bathroom. The Cosy Bar and Restaurant is a substantial end of terrace two storey building The property has been redecorated extensively in recent years and briefly comprises ground floor public bar / restaurant that seats 30+ people and toilets. The first floor provides two bedrooms, bathroom with separate wash up area and an office area. The property is fitted out in a traditional style with solid fuel stove with back boiler fitted. All equipment, fixtures, fittings and furniture are included in the sale.Co-ordinates: 53.9638131,-8.7976885
